South African gross gold and foreign
currency reserves fell 0.7 percent to $50 billion in June from
the previous month, the central bank said.  Net reserves climbed 2.8 to $47.2 billion from $45.9
billion in May, the Pretoria-based Reserve Bank said on its
website today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
